In the 14th year of Emperor Tenmu’s reign (685), Prince Kawashima attained the Rank of Jōdaisan. Among the imperial princes, his status was surpassed only by [[Prince Kusakabe]] (Jōkōichi), [[Prince Ōtsu]] (Jōdaichi), and [[Prince Takatsu]] (Jōkōni)<ref>''Nihon Shoki'', entry for the 14th year of Emperor Tenmu, 1st month, 21st day</ref>. In Shuchō 1 (686), following Emperor Tenmu's death, Prince Kawashima received an additional 100 households as a stipend, bringing his total to 500 households, a Rank comparable to leading officials of the court<ref>''Nihon Shoki'', entry for the 5th year of Empress Jitō, 1st month, 13th day</ref>. He passed away later that year and was interred at Ochi-no in present-day [[Takaichi District]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]].
== Legacy == Prince Kawashima is remembered as a warm and magnanimous individual. His involvement in the [[Prince Ōtsu]] incident has been debated, with some sources suggesting he reported Ōtsu’s alleged rebellion to the court. However, the ''Nihon Shoki'' does not corroborate this, leading scholars to question its veracity<ref>Tokura Yoshitaka, "Prince Ōtsu and His Surroundings," ''Manyōshū Lecture Series'', Vol. 5, Yūseidō, 1973</ref>.
Both the ''[[:en:Kaifūsō|Kaifūsō]]'' and the ''[[Manyōshū]]'' contain works attributed to him, showcasing his talent in poetry and literature. The ''Kaifūsō'' includes one Chinese-style [[wuyan jueju]] poem, while the ''Manyōshū'' features a single Japanese waka attributed to him during [[:en:Empress Jitō|Empress Jitō]]'s 4th-year tour to [[:en:Kii Province|Kii Province]] and [[:en:Ise Province|Ise Province]]<ref>''Manyōshū'', Vol. 1-34</ref>.
== Works == The ''Manyōshū'' contains an elegy by [[:en:Kakinomoto no Hitomaro|Kakinomoto no Hitomaro]] for Prince Kawashima<ref>''Manyōshū'', Vol. 2-194, 195</ref>.
* Elegy presented to Princess Hasebe upon Prince Kawashima's death: ** "Like the seaweed on the u11er reaches of the river Asuka, it sways and intertwines. My lord, whose soft skin I embraced, cannot lie by my side with sword in hand. The night-bed is cold, and I wander alone, wet with morning dew on the fields of Ochi, where we cannot meet again." * [[Tanka]]: ** "The sleeves of our shared bed lie forgotten in Ochi’s fields. Shall we ever meet again?"
== Genealogy == * Father: [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]] * Mother: {{ill|Onokami no Shoryu's daughter|ja|忍海色夫古娘|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onokami no Shoryu's daughter|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ''' Siblings: [[Princess Ōe]], [[Princess Izumi]] * Wife: [[Princess Hasebe]]<ref name=":0">{{cite book|title=Manyōshū, Vol. 2}}</ref> * Children: ** [[Prince Kasuga (son of Prince Kawashima)|Prince Kasuga]] (?-699)<ref>Shioya Kaori, "Doubts about the Genealogy of Prince Shiki," ''Gakushūin Journal'', Vol. 23, 1980</ref> ** [[Prince Mimuro]] (?-745)<ref name="h">{{cite book|author=Suzuki Masatoshi|title=Hundred Family Genealogies, Vol. 10}}</ref> ** [[Prince Takaoka]] (?-749)<ref name="h" />
